    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Montreal Canada E</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>April 18<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 18<add>?</add>7</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(center)">The <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dr Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">It should not have troubled<lb/> you just now when I know your<lb/>
                time must be occupied in your<lb/> great field of labour, but it<lb/> being a matter
                concerning our<lb/> holy Religion, I trust you will<lb/> lend me a helping
                hand.<lb/> A man by the name of <persName>Henry<lb/> Silverstone</persName> has
                applied to me<lb/> to give him <add>חופה וקידושין</add> on my<lb/> objecting to
                grant his request,<lb/> on the grounds of having heard<lb/> that he had a Wife in
                    <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>,<lb/> he then produced me a letter<lb/> from
                a <persName>Michael Eakerman</persName> his</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Brother in Law of that City<lb/> to say that <persName>Mr
                Silverston's</persName><lb/> Wife died on the <date>24<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of
                    March<lb/> 1866</date> as I should like to have<lb/> stronger evidence than
                that<lb/> letter before giving the said<lb/>
                <persName>Silverstone</persName>
                <add>חופה וקידושין</add> any in<lb/>formation you could give<lb/> me in the matter
                would be<lb/> thankfully acknowledged by<lb/> all parties</p>
            <p>Allow me to thank you for<lb/> the Occident you so kindly<lb/> forwarded to me, you
                will<lb/> now be good to let me know<lb/> in your next the terms, and how<lb/> I am
                to remit to you the yearly<lb/> subscription for it. Trusting<lb/> that this may
                find you in the<lb/> enjoyment of improved health</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">Believe me to be</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Dr Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Yours truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">M P Cohen</persName>
            </p>
            <p>Minister</p>
            <p>English &amp; German Congregation</p>
            <p
                rend="The following text is written sideways over the previous text, in the upper left corner of the page."
                >Be good enough to hand over the<lb/> enclosed to the party could you make it<lb/>
                convenient</p>
        </body>
